data.title: StatePlaneToLatLon()
data.text:
Notes: Â

Â Â Â - If unfamiliar with Excel vector functions, see Vector Functions reference

Â Â Â - State plane coordinates are often provided in feet. Â Be sure to convert to meters before using this function. Â Also note that most state plane coordinates are in U.S. Survey Feet (3937 yards = 3600 meters). Â This is slightly different than the more common international foot (1 foot = 0.3048 meters). Â If you are not doing very high precision work, the slight difference between these two conversions will not matter.

Â Â Â - The list of Â state codes follows the convention in SPCS83, reproduced below.

Â Â Â - By special request, this function can also convert from Minnesota County Coordinates. Â See below for county codes.
